24. Rad1 Ra7 25. Ne3 Qh5 26. Nd4 Bxg2 27. Kxg2 Qe5 28. Nc4 Qc5 29. Nc6 Rc7 30.
Ne3 Ne5 31. R1d5 ({Black correctly gave up, but maybe a bit early. Personally
I would have tried} 31. R1d5 Nc4 32. Rxc5 Nxb2 {but objectively White wins,
for example} 33. Rc2 Rxe3 (33... Na4 34. Nd5 $18) 34. fxe3 $18 {and with an
